{
  "stem": "22979.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The death march?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it could be in a half an hour.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would like very much because I-- just, you know, we're talking and so many things happened in one day, in one hour, in one minute.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it's hard to-- to-- you know, to get to everything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I would actually like to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had in Auschwitz, in Birkenau, when I was still in the-- in the camp with the rest of the population-- I would say the inmates population, the inmates together-- besides us Jews-- I mentioned there were Aryan too.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were Polish women.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were German brought in extra who were for political reasons there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there were also Jehovah's Witnesses, you know, [INAUDIBLE], but they were very privileged.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They didn't-- they worked as maids or nannies in the households of the SS.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were all too women from quite a large group, women from the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Ukraine women, they were exposed already to very, very harsh life during the Communist era in Russia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they were really survivors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they worked in separate units, not with Jews together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the Germans treated them even worse like Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's-- that's-- I have to say.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were getting the worst jobs, carrying demolition houses, carrying stones, working the hardest job in the factories.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But beside being in the same place with Jews, with us, they were very, very, very much anti-Semitic, even in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "If some of the Ukrainians-- you know, it happened that they worked together with Jewish laborers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They were always mean, and if they could hit or torture a Jewish girl, they did.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
